WEBVTT

00:02.377 --> 00:02.798
<i>(OWL HOOTS)</i>

00:09.801 --> 00:10.802
(SCREECHES)

00:12.554 --> 00:13.680
<i>Adventure Time</i>

00:13.764 --> 00:15.061
<i>Come on, grab your friends</i>

00:15.140 --> 00:18.019
<i>We're going to a very distant land</i>

00:18.018 --> 00:20.146
<i>With Finn and Jake and Marceline</i>

00:20.229 --> 00:22.152
<i>And Princess Bubblegum</i>

00:22.231 --> 00:23.904
<i>It's Adventure Time</i>

00:34.451 --> 00:36.829
(PANTING) Marceline, no!

00:37.079 --> 00:41.209
Don't let anyone read my diaries!
Burn them, Finn! They're embarrassi...

00:41.291 --> 00:42.588
(SCREAMING)

00:44.461 --> 00:46.088
And then he said, "Fine."

00:46.713 --> 00:48.340
That's the story of how I met your dad.

00:49.216 --> 00:50.217
Can I play now?

00:50.592 --> 00:52.970
No, Marceline, sweetie. It's nap time.

00:53.470 --> 00:56.349
But I don't want to sleep.
My dreams are weird.

00:56.807 --> 00:58.229
All dreams are weird.

00:58.350 --> 01:02.605
But, Mom, my dreams are weird!

01:02.688 --> 01:03.735
(CHUCKLES)

01:03.730 --> 01:06.574
Honey, something weird might
just be something familiar

01:06.650 --> 01:07.776
viewed from a different angle.

01:07.901 --> 01:09.699
And that's not scary, right?

01:11.530 --> 01:13.703
<i>(SINGING) Let's go in the garden</i>

01:14.324 --> 01:16.452
<i>You'll find something waiting</i>

01:17.077 --> 01:19.205
<i>BOTH: Right there where you left it</i>

01:19.538 --> 01:21.916
<i>Flying upside down</i>

01:22.666 --> 01:24.794
<i>When you finally find it</i>

01:25.460 --> 01:27.679
<i>You'll see how it's faded</i>

01:27.963 --> 01:30.307
<i>The underside is lighter</i>

01:30.465 --> 01:32.593
<i>When you turn it around</i>

01:32.843 --> 01:36.814
<i>Everything stays right where you left it</i>

01:37.723 --> 01:38.975
ICE KING: Hello, Marcy.

01:39.474 --> 01:41.602
I don't know if you'll ever hear this message.

01:42.060 --> 01:44.233
I fear my thoughts are no longer my own.

01:44.730 --> 01:46.357
Just watch over me

01:46.440 --> 01:49.489
until I can find my way out
of this labyrinth in my brain

01:49.568 --> 01:51.366
and regain my sanity.

01:51.820 --> 01:54.243
And then maybe, Betty, my princess,

01:54.740 --> 01:56.959
maybe you will love me again.

01:57.242 --> 02:00.246
(SIGHS) Please love me again, Betty!

02:00.495 --> 02:01.997
(SOBBING)

02:03.373 --> 02:04.374
Okay!

02:05.876 --> 02:07.002
- (CAMERA SHATFERS)
- (SIGHS)

02:07.878 --> 02:11.303
Hey, Simon. I, uh, finished packing your gear.

02:11.757 --> 02:13.259
So, can I have my tape now?

02:13.383 --> 02:14.680
What? No.

02:14.801 --> 02:16.428
This is private, silly.

02:16.678 --> 02:18.806
There you go. Snug as a bug.

02:19.431 --> 02:21.433
Seriously, Simon. Please don't go.

02:22.059 --> 02:24.187
I... I have to protect you.

02:24.561 --> 02:26.814
How can you protect me
if you're not even here?

02:27.064 --> 02:29.158
I'll arrange for someone
to come take care of you.

02:29.941 --> 02:31.443
I'll make sure he doesn't leave.

02:32.319 --> 02:34.447
Please, Simon, I could help you with this.

02:34.780 --> 02:37.203
Yeah. Maybe one day you will.

02:37.658 --> 02:41.708
But until then, you have to stay
brave, my fearless Marceline.

02:43.580 --> 02:44.581
- (BREAKS)
- Ouch!

02:45.207 --> 02:46.834
You see? I have to go now.

02:47.334 --> 02:48.586
Good bye, Marcy.

02:48.585 --> 02:50.587
Wait! No! Wait!

02:50.587 --> 02:51.588
(GROANS)

02:51.963 --> 02:52.964
Simon!

02:53.298 --> 02:54.299
Simon!

02:54.841 --> 02:56.559
(WIND HOWLING)

03:00.597 --> 03:01.849
(GROWLS)

03:02.182 --> 03:04.105
(PANTING) Ugh, ew.

03:05.727 --> 03:07.104
(LAUGHING MANIACALLY)

03:07.229 --> 03:09.106
Okay, I know you're here.

03:09.731 --> 03:10.698
(LAUGHING CONTINUES)

03:18.615 --> 03:19.741
Peek-a-pop! (LAUGHS)

03:19.825 --> 03:20.872
The Fool!

03:20.951 --> 03:22.248
(LAUGHS)

03:22.869 --> 03:24.371
You found me, Marceline!

03:24.746 --> 03:26.248
Now you're it.

03:26.456 --> 03:30.131
We're not playing, Fool.
You're an evil, blood-sucking fiend.

03:30.210 --> 03:32.258
I'm trying to kill you.

03:33.505 --> 03:34.757
Hey, you want to see something funny?

03:35.215 --> 03:36.762
(INHALES DEEPLY)

03:36.758 --> 03:37.884
I look like a butt.

03:38.009 --> 03:39.101
(BLOWS RASPBERRY)

03:40.512 --> 03:42.389
" Argh!
<i>'</i> (LAUGHS)

03:42.514 --> 03:43.982
(COUGHING)

03:45.475 --> 03:46.522
Huh? (SNIFFS)

03:50.397 --> 03:52.399
(LAUGHING MANIACALLY)

03:55.360 --> 03:56.612
Oh. Cool.

04:00.615 --> 04:02.538
Sweet music to my ears.

04:02.534 --> 04:04.002
(BASS PLAYS)

04:08.540 --> 04:10.167
Come on, little bun.

04:10.667 --> 04:12.385
Just turn around.

04:14.671 --> 04:16.389
Ugh, stupid animal.

04:22.012 --> 04:23.013
What?

04:23.138 --> 04:25.015
Oh! I'm sorry!

04:25.766 --> 04:27.143
All right, hold still.

04:28.602 --> 04:29.649
There you go.

04:30.228 --> 04:31.525
See? It's okay.

04:34.649 --> 04:35.650
(SCREAMING)

04:36.401 --> 04:39.154
No, kid! You don't have to be afraid of me!

04:39.237 --> 04:41.535
I'm a really good person.

04:41.656 --> 04:42.657
(INDISTINCT CONVERSATIONS)

04:43.241 --> 04:46.290
GUYS, GUYS, GUYS, GUYS, GUYS,
GUYS, GUYS, GUYS, GUYS, GUYS, GUYS!

04:46.411 --> 04:47.412
ALL: Huh?

04:47.496 --> 04:51.046
There's... (PANTING) A vampire!

04:51.124 --> 04:52.171
ALL: No!

04:52.167 --> 04:54.295
Yes way. I saw it real close.

04:54.544 --> 04:57.673
It looked like a girl, but it had fangs like...

04:57.672 --> 04:59.049
(GRUMBLING)

05:00.050 --> 05:01.552
Everybody, ready your weapons.

05:02.052 --> 05:04.054
Don't worry. We'll be ready for it.

05:04.179 --> 05:05.431
(BIRD SQUAWKING)

05:05.514 --> 05:06.561
(GRUNTS)

05:07.557 --> 05:09.059
(GASPS) Hey.

05:09.392 --> 05:10.689
(ALL GASP)

05:10.894 --> 05:13.773
No, no, I... It's cool. I'm on your side.

05:14.564 --> 05:16.066
(WHIMPERS)

05:16.441 --> 05:17.784
Go away, vampire.

05:18.193 --> 05:21.538
I'm in the sunlight. I'm not a flipping vampire!

05:22.030 --> 05:23.532
(ALL SCREAMING)

05:25.951 --> 05:26.918
(SIGHS)

05:30.580 --> 05:31.832
Mmm? Mmm?

05:32.290 --> 05:33.212
What's that?

05:33.458 --> 05:36.587
Oh, you want old Two Bread Tom
to play the song.

05:36.962 --> 05:38.839
Please do not play the song.

05:39.214 --> 05:40.591
No, the child is right.

05:40.966 --> 05:43.594
As humans, it's our duty to tell the tales,

05:44.177 --> 05:45.224
to sing the songs.

05:45.804 --> 05:47.431
Art must survive.

05:49.224 --> 05:51.352
<i>(SINGING) Streaks on the china</i>

05:51.476 --> 05:53.478
<i>Never mattered before</i>

05:53.603 --> 05:54.980
<i>Who cares?</i>

05:54.980 --> 05:56.982
<i>When you drop-kicked your jacket</i>

05:57.357 --> 05:59.234
<i>As you came through the door</i>

05:59.234 --> 06:00.611
<i>No one glared</i>

06:00.986 --> 06:04.115
BOTH: <i>But sometimes
things get turned around</i>

06:04.114 --> 06:06.742
<i>And no one's spared</i>

06:07.117 --> 06:10.246
<i>(SINGING ALONE)
All hands, look out below</i>

06:10.245 --> 06:13.374
<i>There's a change in the status quo</i>

06:13.373 --> 06:17.628
<i>Gonna need all the help
that we can get</i>

06:17.627 --> 06:18.628
(GIRL COUGHS)

06:22.716 --> 06:23.888
(GROWLS)

06:29.514 --> 06:31.266
(IMITATES GUITAR)

06:32.392 --> 06:33.769
You want me to play more?

06:34.144 --> 06:35.612
TWO BREAD TOM: Yes, please.

06:35.896 --> 06:37.773
The consensus is that your cover's better.

06:39.149 --> 06:42.153
(SINGING) <i>According to our new arrival</i>

06:42.277 --> 06:45.656
<i>Life is more than mere survival</i>

06:45.780 --> 06:49.159
<i>And we just might live the good life yet</i>

06:51.369 --> 06:52.996
(BASS PLAYING)

06:55.123 --> 06:56.045
Hmm?

06:56.291 --> 06:59.795
Oh, man, Schwabl, I sure hope
there ain't a little vampire kid

06:59.794 --> 07:00.920
sneaking up behind me.

07:01.046 --> 07:02.298
Vampire attack!

07:02.547 --> 07:03.764
Oh, no!

07:04.424 --> 07:05.926
- Ugh! I'm dead.
- (SPITS)

07:07.010 --> 07:08.637
This is serious, Marceline.

07:08.929 --> 07:12.650
What if I was a vampire?
You need an animal hat.

07:16.311 --> 07:18.655
Looks like the project's coming along, huh?

07:18.939 --> 07:19.940
- (FOGHORN BLARES)
- (IMITATES FOGHORN)

07:23.902 --> 07:24.903
(MARCELINE WHISTLES)

07:25.070 --> 07:26.572
BOTH: Hey, Marceline!

07:27.030 --> 07:29.658
Two Bread Torn, how's it going, man?

07:29.824 --> 07:32.452
Oh, so good. I had a hoagie for lunch.

07:32.827 --> 07:35.296
And even better, the ship's
repairs are almost done.

07:35.538 --> 07:37.791
We should be ready to sail
in another day or two.

07:38.083 --> 07:39.835
Oh, that's really great.

07:40.210 --> 07:43.589
But listen, I've cleared out
almost all the vampires that are left.

07:44.089 --> 07:46.968
In another week or two,
you won't even have to leave.

07:47.217 --> 07:49.561
Yeah, Marceline!

07:49.844 --> 07:52.688
Oh, Marcy, you're such a sweet weird kid.

07:53.098 --> 07:56.978
But it's not just the vampires or the oozers
or them hungry-looking rainbows.

07:57.727 --> 08:00.105
The latest atmospheric readings
are going bananas.

08:00.605 --> 08:01.982
Something big is coming.

08:02.065 --> 08:04.318
And it's gonna change all of this.

08:04.859 --> 08:07.362
No, we'd do best to clear out
of this continent altogether.

08:07.988 --> 08:10.741
Hey, you should come, too.
After all, you're one of us.

08:11.074 --> 08:12.121
(BELL CLANKING)

08:12.575 --> 08:14.077
They're here! They're here!

08:15.245 --> 08:17.464
Ahhh! He's biting my hat!

08:18.957 --> 08:20.129
Get to the boat!

08:20.500 --> 08:22.252
(VAMPIRES GRUMBLING)

08:31.136 --> 08:32.136
(CHUCKLES)

08:33.388 --> 08:35.061
Oh, jeez. Oh, jeez.

08:35.432 --> 08:36.933
That's not Schwabl, man.

08:37.267 --> 08:38.563
(LAUGHS EVILLY)

08:39.519 --> 08:41.066
Well, you got me.

08:41.062 --> 08:42.938
What gave it away? The boots?

08:46.943 --> 08:47.944
Ahhh!

08:51.322 --> 08:52.665
Marceline!

08:53.658 --> 08:54.705
Whoa, whoa!

08:55.702 --> 08:57.579
Hi, there, Hierophant!

08:58.079 --> 09:02.585
Why can't you just let us eat humans?
You're, like, messing up the natural order.

09:02.834 --> 09:04.962
This is our time.

09:05.295 --> 09:06.672
It's my time.

09:06.838 --> 09:09.967
And once I stake and gank
your shape-shifting power,

09:10.216 --> 09:12.218
I'll be unstoppable.

09:12.469 --> 09:13.937
- (SWORDS CLANGING)
- Ha!

09:14.596 --> 09:16.439
(GASPS) What?

09:16.723 --> 09:17.724
(LAUGHS)

09:17.974 --> 09:20.102
I picked up self-healing power last month,

09:20.185 --> 09:22.608
off some vamp with a head
like a garden trowel.

09:22.854 --> 09:25.733
So, you've slain Sister Moon.

09:25.982 --> 09:29.111
Look at you. You're just a hapa demon punk,

09:29.736 --> 09:33.366
blind to the price you must
pay for such powers.

09:34.074 --> 09:35.997
(IMITATES DRACULA) Blah! I don't care!

09:36.367 --> 09:37.368
Fine.

09:39.871 --> 09:41.248
Ah! Show yourself!

09:41.706 --> 09:42.753
Okay.

09:43.208 --> 09:44.209
Wah-wah.

09:46.836 --> 09:47.837
(GULPS)

09:48.463 --> 09:50.090
(LAUGHS EVILLY)

09:51.966 --> 09:53.639
Ka-ching!

09:55.762 --> 09:57.139
(GASPS)

09:58.348 --> 09:59.395
Oh, jeez.

09:59.849 --> 10:02.352
Hey, Marceline, let me "ax" you something.

10:02.477 --> 10:03.649
(LAUGHS) You get it?

10:04.771 --> 10:06.114
You have to leave, Tom.

10:06.397 --> 10:08.240
Oh, I didn't think it was that bad.

10:08.525 --> 10:10.653
You have to leave now!

10:10.652 --> 10:11.653
Ahhh!

10:11.861 --> 10:12.862
He's here.

10:13.613 --> 10:15.240
He's the worst of them all.

10:16.157 --> 10:17.158
The Vampire King.

10:19.744 --> 10:20.745
(SCREAMING)

10:22.539 --> 10:23.506
What?

10:27.043 --> 10:29.671
Marceline, you're not dead! Whoo!

10:30.130 --> 10:33.054
PB's cure. It must have worked!

10:33.800 --> 10:35.177
No soy vampire.

10:35.927 --> 10:37.520
Also, untie me, please.

10:38.263 --> 10:39.435
I'm not a murderer!

10:40.056 --> 10:42.809
Okay, but wait, if she's not a vampire,

10:43.184 --> 10:45.186
then what's been draining our cows?

10:46.688 --> 10:47.940
(GROANS)

10:48.273 --> 10:49.445
Ahhh!

10:49.816 --> 10:50.942
Finn?

10:52.569 --> 10:53.695
Finn?

10:54.320 --> 10:57.824
Jeez. I hope Finn didn't get
blood-sucked after I stress-fainted.

11:02.829 --> 11:04.046
Who the heck is this?

11:06.457 --> 11:08.209
(MELLOW MUSIC PLAYS)

11:10.086 --> 11:11.554
(HISSES)

11:26.352 --> 11:28.571
This party's so crazy!
